45/* finite field arithmetic operations */
46
47#define f2(x) ((x<<1) ^ (((x>>7) & 1) * WPOLY))
48#define f4(x) ((x<<2) ^ (((x>>6) & 1) * WPOLY) ^ (((x>>6) & 2) * WPOLY))
49#define f8(x) ((x<<3) ^ (((x>>5) & 1) * WPOLY) ^ (((x>>5) & 2) * WPOLY) \
50 ^ (((x>>5) & 4) * WPOLY))
51#define f3(x) (f2(x) ^ x)
52#define f9(x) (f8(x) ^ x)
53#define fb(x) (f8(x) ^ f2(x) ^ x)
54#define fd(x) (f8(x) ^ f4(x) ^ x)
55#define fe(x) (f8(x) ^ f4(x) ^ f2(x))
56
57#endif
58

163#define h0(x) (x)
164
165/* These defines are used to ensure tables are generated in the
166 right format depending on the internal byte order required
167*/
168
169#define w0(p) bytes2word(p, 0, 0, 0)
170#define w1(p) bytes2word(0, p, 0, 0)
171#define w2(p) bytes2word(0, 0, p, 0)
172#define w3(p) bytes2word(0, 0, 0, p)
173
174/* Number of elements required in this table for different
175 block and key lengths is:
176
177 Rcon Table key length (bytes)
178 Length 16 20 24 28 32
179 ---------------------
180 block 16 | 10 9 8 7 7
181 length 20 | 14 11 10 9 9
182 (bytes) 24 | 19 15 12 11 11
183 28 | 24 19 16 13 13
184 32 | 29 23 19 17 14
185
186 this table can be a table of bytes if the key schedule
187 code is adjusted accordingly
188*/
189
190#define u0(p) bytes2word(f2(p), p, p, f3(p))
191#define u1(p) bytes2word(f3(p), f2(p), p, p)
192#define u2(p) bytes2word(p, f3(p), f2(p), p)
193#define u3(p) bytes2word(p, p, f3(p), f2(p))
194
195#define v0(p) bytes2word(fe(p), f9(p), fd(p), fb(p))
196#define v1(p) bytes2word(fb(p), fe(p), f9(p), fd(p))
197#define v2(p) bytes2word(fd(p), fb(p), fe(p), f9(p))
198#define v3(p) bytes2word(f9(p), fd(p), fb(p), fe(p))
199
200const aes_32t t_dec(r,c)[RC_LENGTH] =
201{
202 w0(0x01), w0(0x02), w0(0x04), w0(0x08), w0(0x10),
203 w0(0x20), w0(0x40), w0(0x80), w0(0x1b), w0(0x36),
204#if RC_LENGTH > 10
205 w0(0x6c), w0(0xd8), w0(0xab), w0(0x4d),
206#endif
207#if RC_LENGTH > 14
208 w0(0x9a), w0(0x2f), w0(0x5e), w0(0xbc), w0(0x63),
209#endif
210#if RC_LENGTH > 19
211 w0(0xc6), w0(0x97), w0(0x35), w0(0x6a), w0(0xd4),
212#endif
213#if RC_LENGTH > 24
214 w0(0xb3), w0(0x7d), w0(0xfa), w0(0xef), w0(0xc5)
215#endif
216};

336/* Generate the tables for the dynamic table option
337
338 It will generally be sensible to use tables to compute finite
339 field multiplies and inverses but where memory is scarse this
340 code might sometimes be better. But it only has effect during
341 initialisation so its pretty unimportant in overall terms.
342*/
343
344/* return 2 ^ (n - 1) where n is the bit number of the highest bit
345 set in x with x in the range 1 < x < 0x00000200. This form is
346 used so that locals within fi can be bytes rather than words
347*/
348
349static aes_08t hibit(const aes_32t x)
350{ aes_08t r = (aes_08t)((x >> 1) | (x >> 2));
351
352 r |= (r >> 2);
353 r |= (r >> 4);
354 return (r + 1) >> 1;
355}
356
357/* return the inverse of the finite field element x */
358
359static aes_08t fi(const aes_08t x)
360{ aes_08t p1 = x, p2 = BPOLY, n1 = hibit(x), n2 = 0x80, v1 = 1, v2 = 0;
361
362 if(x < 2) return x;
363
364 for(;;)
365 {
366 if(!n1) return v1;
367
368 while(n2 >= n1)
369 {
370 n2 /= n1; p2 ^= p1 * n2; v2 ^= v1 * n2; n2 = hibit(p2);
371 }
372
373 if(!n2) return v2;
374
375 while(n1 >= n2)
376 {
377 n1 /= n2; p1 ^= p2 * n1; v1 ^= v2 * n1; n1 = hibit(p1);
378 }
379 }
380}
381
382#else
383
384/* define the finite field multiplies required for Rijndael */
385
386#define f2(x) ((x) ? pow[log[x] + 0x19] : 0)
387#define f3(x) ((x) ? pow[log[x] + 0x01] : 0)
388#define f9(x) ((x) ? pow[log[x] + 0xc7] : 0)
389#define fb(x) ((x) ? pow[log[x] + 0x68] : 0)
390#define fd(x) ((x) ? pow[log[x] + 0xee] : 0)
391#define fe(x) ((x) ? pow[log[x] + 0xdf] : 0)
392#define fi(x) ((x) ? pow[255 - log[x]]: 0)
393
394#endif
395
396/* The forward and inverse affine transformations used in the S-box */
397
398#define fwd_affine(x) \
399 (w = (aes_32t)x, w ^= (w<<1)^(w<<2)^(w<<3)^(w<<4), 0x63^(aes_08t)(w^(w>>8)))
400
401#define inv_affine(x) \
402 (w = (aes_32t)x, w = (w<<1)^(w<<3)^(w<<6), 0x05^(aes_08t)(w^(w>>8)))
403
404#ifdef GLOBALS
405void gen_tabs(void)
406#else
407void gen_tabs(aes_ctx cx[1])
408#endif
409{ aes_32t i, w;
410
411#if defined(FF_TABLES)
412
413 aes_08t pow[512], log[256];
414
415 /* log and power tables for GF(2^8) finite field with
416 WPOLY as modular polynomial - the simplest primitive
417 root is 0x03, used here to generate the tables
418 */
419
420 i = 0; w = 1;
421 do
422 {
423 pow[i] = (aes_08t)w;
424 pow[i + 255] = (aes_08t)w;
425 log[w] = (aes_08t)i++;
426 w ^= (w << 1) ^ (w & 0x80 ? WPOLY : 0);
427 }
428 while (w != 1);
429
430#endif
431
432#ifndef GLOBALS
433 if(!cx->t_ptr)
434 cx->t_ptr = &s_t;
435#endif
436
437 for(i = 0, w = 1; i < RC_LENGTH; ++i)
438 {
439 t_set(r,c)[i] = bytes2word(w, 0, 0, 0);
440 w = f2(w);
441 }
442
443 for(i = 0; i < 256; ++i)
444 { aes_08t b;
445
446 b = fwd_affine(fi((aes_08t)i));
447 w = bytes2word(f2(b), b, b, f3(b));
448
449#ifdef SBX_SET
450 t_set(s,box)[i] = b;
451#endif
452
453#ifdef FT1_SET /* tables for a normal encryption round */
454 t_set(f,n)[i] = w;
455#endif
456#ifdef FT4_SET
457 t_set(f,n)[0][i] = w;
458 t_set(f,n)[1][i] = upr(w,1);
459 t_set(f,n)[2][i] = upr(w,2);
460 t_set(f,n)[3][i] = upr(w,3);
461#endif
462 w = bytes2word(b, 0, 0, 0);
463
464#ifdef FL1_SET /* tables for last encryption round (may also */
465 t_set(f,l)[i] = w; /* be used in the key schedule) */
466#endif
467#ifdef FL4_SET
468 t_set(f,l)[0][i] = w;
469 t_set(f,l)[1][i] = upr(w,1);
470 t_set(f,l)[2][i] = upr(w,2);
471 t_set(f,l)[3][i] = upr(w,3);
472#endif
473
474#ifdef LS1_SET /* table for key schedule if t_set(f,l) above is */
475 t_set(l,s)[i] = w; /* not of the required form */
476#endif
477#ifdef LS4_SET
478 t_set(l,s)[0][i] = w;
479 t_set(l,s)[1][i] = upr(w,1);
480 t_set(l,s)[2][i] = upr(w,2);
481 t_set(l,s)[3][i] = upr(w,3);
482#endif
483
484 b = fi(inv_affine((aes_08t)i));
485 w = bytes2word(fe(b), f9(b), fd(b), fb(b));
486
487#ifdef IM1_SET /* tables for the inverse mix column operation */
488 t_set(i,m)[b] = w;
489#endif
490#ifdef IM4_SET
491 t_set(i,m)[0][b] = w;
492 t_set(i,m)[1][b] = upr(w,1);
493 t_set(i,m)[2][b] = upr(w,2);
494 t_set(i,m)[3][b] = upr(w,3);
495#endif
496
497#ifdef ISB_SET
498 t_set(i,box)[i] = b;
499#endif
500#ifdef IT1_SET /* tables for a normal decryption round */
501 t_set(i,n)[i] = w;
502#endif
503#ifdef IT4_SET
504 t_set(i,n)[0][i] = w;
505 t_set(i,n)[1][i] = upr(w,1);
506 t_set(i,n)[2][i] = upr(w,2);
507 t_set(i,n)[3][i] = upr(w,3);
508#endif
509 w = bytes2word(b, 0, 0, 0);
510#ifdef IL1_SET /* tables for last decryption round */
511 t_set(i,l)[i] = w;
512#endif
513#ifdef IL4_SET
514 t_set(i,l)[0][i] = w;
515 t_set(i,l)[1][i] = upr(w,1);
516 t_set(i,l)[2][i] = upr(w,2);
517 t_set(i,l)[3][i] = upr(w,3);
518#endif
519 }
520
521 t_set(in,it) = 1;
522}
523
524#endif
525
526#if defined(__cplusplus)
527}
528#endif
